comment: Properties to check if a Dart application is running on server-side or client-side, Dart browsers or other JS browsers. Since This library uses 'dart:html'. This can only be imported by client applications.

children.name: isJsClient
children.comment: Determines whether or not the running program is JavaScript or DartScript.

children.name: isDartClient
children.comment: Determines whether or not the running program is DartScript or JavaScript.

children.name: isServer
children.comment:
Returns true when running a plain Dart VM. This might happen when 
running shared code on the server, or during the console unit-testing.
Returns false if this code is running inside the normal browser 
environment, either as development or production code.

children.name: isClient
children.comment:
Returns true when running inside the normal browser environment, 
either as development or production code. Returns false 
if this code is running in a plain Dart VM. This might happen when 
running shared code on the server, or during the console unit-testing.

children.comment: Determines whether or not the running program is JavaScript or DartScript.
